fields.name: KEY
fields.desc: Stores AES keys.

fields.name: TEXT_IN
fields.desc: Stores the source data when the AES accelerator operates in the Typical AES working mode.

fields.name: TEXT_OUT
fields.desc: Stores the result data when the AES accelerator operates in the Typical AES working mode.

fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: Defines the key length and the encryption/decryption of the AES accelerator.

fields.name: TRIGGER
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to start AES calculation.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: Stores the working status of the AES accelerator. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

1610850384.name: IV_MEM[%s]
1610850384.desc: The memory that stores initialization vector

1610850400.name: H_MEM[%s]
1610850400.desc: The memory that stores GCM hash subkey

fields.name: DMA_ENABLE
fields.desc: Defines the working mode of the AES accelerator. 1'b0: typical AES working mode, 1'b1: DMA-AES working mode.

fields.name: BLOCK_MODE
fields.desc: Defines the block cipher mode of the AES accelerator operating under the DMA-AES working mode. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: reserved, 0x7: reserved.

fields.name: BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Stores the Block Number of plaintext or ciphertext when the AES accelerator operates under the DMA-AES working mode.

fields.name: INC_SEL
fields.desc: Defines the Standard Incrementing Function for CTR block operation. Set this bit to 0 or 1 to choose INC32 or INC128.

1610850464.name: AAD_BLOCK_NUM
1610850464.desc: Additional Authential Data block number register

fields.name: AAD_BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of AAD block.

fields.name: REMAINDER_BIT_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of remainder bit.

fields.name: CONTINUE
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to continue GCM operation.

fields.name: INT_CLEAR
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to clear AES interrupt.

fields.name: INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable AES interrupt and 0 to disable interrupt. This field is only effective for DMA-AES operation.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This bits stores the version information of AES.

fields.name: DMA_EXIT
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to exit AES operation. This field is only effective for DMA-AES operation.

fields.name: WRITEBACK_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set 1 to bypass cache writeback request to external memory so that spi will not check its attribute.

fields.name: FLASH_PAGE_SIZE
fields.desc: Set the page size of the used MSPI flash. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

fields.name: SRAM_PAGE_SIZE
fields.desc: Set the page size of the used MSPI external RAM. 0: 256 bytes. 1: 512 bytes. 2: 1024 bytes. 3: 2048 bytes.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Version control

1610870792.name: IN_INT_RAW_CH%s
1610870792.desc: Raw status interrupt of Rx channel 0

fields.name: IN_DONE
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0. For UHCI0, the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data error is detected only in the case that the peripheral is UHCI0 for Rx channel 0. For other peripherals, this raw interrupt is reserved.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting inlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of inlink descriptor for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Rx buffer pointed by inlink is full and receiving data is not completed, but there is no more inlink for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: INFIFO_FULL_WM
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when received data byte number is up to threshold configured by REG_DMA_INFIFO_FULL_THRS_CH0 in Rx FIFO of channel 0.

fields.name: INFIFO_OVF_L1
fields.desc: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is overflow.

fields.name: INFIFO_UDF_L1
fields.desc: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

fields.name: INFIFO_OVF_L3
fields.desc: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 3 fifo of Rx channel 0 is overflow.

fields.name: INFIFO_UDF_L3
fields.desc: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 3 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

fields.desc: The bit is used to enable lock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after lock operation done.

fields.name: DCACHE_UNLOCK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable unlock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after unlock operation done.

fields.name: DCACHE_LOCK_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate unlock/lock operation is finished.

fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the start virtual address for lock operations. It should be combined with DCACHE_LOCK_SIZE_REG.

fields.name: DCACHE_LOCK_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the length for lock operations. The bits are the counts of cache block. It should be combined with DCACHE_LOCK_ADDR_REG.

fields.desc: The bit is used to enable invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after invalidate operation done.

fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate clean/writeback/invalidate operation is finished.

fields.name: DCACHE_SYNC_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the length for sync operations. The bits are the counts of cache block. It should be combined with DCACHE_SYNC_ADDR_REG.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable and disable autoload operation. It is combined with icache_autoload_done. 1: enable, 0: disable.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate autoload operation is finished.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_ORDER
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the direction of autoload. 1: descending, 0: ascending.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_RQST
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure trigger conditions for autoload. 0/3: cache miss, 1: cache hit, 2: both cache miss and hit.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the numbers of the cache block for the issuing autoload operation.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_BUFFER_CLEAR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear autoload buffer in icache.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_ADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the first section for autoload operation. It should be combined with icache_autoload_sct0_ena.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT0_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the length of the first section for autoload operation. It should be combined with icache_autoload_sct0_ena.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_ADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the second section for autoload operation. It should be combined with icache_autoload_sct1_ena.

fields.name: ICACHE_AUTOLOAD_SCT1_SIZE
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the length of the second section for autoload operation. It should be combined with icache_autoload_sct1_ena.

fields.name: IBUS_TO_FLASH_START_VADDR

fields.name: IBUS_TO_FLASH_END_VADDR

fields.name: DBUS_TO_FLASH_START_VADDR

fields.name: DBUS_TO_FLASH_END_VADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to configure the end virtual address of dbus to access flash. The register is used to give constraints to dbus access counter.

fields.name: ICACHE_ACS_CNT_CLR

fields.name: DBUS_ACS_FLASH_MISS_CNT

fields.name: DBUS_ACS_CNT

fields.name: CACHE_MMU_FAULT_CODE
fields.desc: The right-most 3 bits are used to indicate the operations which cause mmu fault occurrence. 0: default, 1: cpu miss, 2: preload miss, 3: writeback, 4: cpu miss evict recovery address, 5: load miss evict recovery address, 6: external dma tx, 7: external dma rx. The most significant bit is used to indicate this operation occurs in which one icache.

fields.name: CACHE_MMU_FAULT_VADDR
fields.desc: The bits are used to indicate the virtual address which cause mmu fault..

fields.name: CACHE_MMU_MEM_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable clock gating to save power when access mmu memory, 0: enable, 1: disable

fields.name: CACHE_MMU_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: The bit is used to power mmu memory down, 0: follow_rtc_lslp_pd, 1: power up

fields.desc:
This is the content of command 0. It consists of three parts: 
op_code is the command, 0: RSTART; 1: WRITE; 2: READ; 3: STOP; 4: END.
Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.
ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more
Information.

fields.name: RX_PCM_CONF
fields.desc: I2S RX compress/decompress configuration bit. & 0 (atol): A-Law decompress, 1 (ltoa) : A-Law compress, 2 (utol) : u-Law decompress, 3 (ltou) : u-Law compress. &

fields.name: RX_PCM_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to bypass Compress/Decompress module for received data.

fields.name: RX_LEFT_ALIGN

fields.name: RX_24_FILL_EN

fields.name: RX_WS_IDLE_POL
fields.desc: 0: WS should be 0 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

fields.name: RX_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: I2S Rx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is received first. 0:big endian, the MSB is received first.

fields.name: RX_TDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S TDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: RX_PDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S PDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: TX_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset transmitter

fields.name: TX_FIFO_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset Tx AFIFO

fields.name: TX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start transmitting data

fields.name: TX_SLAVE_MOD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable slave transmitter mode

fields.name: TX_MONO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable transmitter in mono mode

fields.name: TX_CHAN_EQUAL

fields.name: TX_BIG_ENDIAN

fields.name: RX_CLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: I2S Rx module clock enable signal.

fields.name: RX_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: Select I2S Rx module source clock. 0: no clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.name: MCLK_SEL
fields.desc: 0: UseI2S Tx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.  1: UseI2S Rx module clock as I2S_MCLK_OUT.

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral I2S TX clock divider value. f_I2S_CLK = f_I2S_CLK_S/(N+b/a). There will be (a-b) * n-div and b * (n+1)-div.  So the average combination will be:  for b <= a/2, z * [x * n-div + (n+1)-div] + y * n-div. For b > a/2, z * [n-div + x * (n+1)-div] + y * (n+1)-div.

fields.name: TX_CLK_ACTIVE
fields.desc: I2S Tx module clock enable signal.

fields.name: TX_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: Select I2S Tx module source clock. 0: XTAL clock. 1: APLL. 2: CLK160. 3: I2S_MCLK_in.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable clk gate

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_Z
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is b. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Z is (a-b).

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_Y
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%b) . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_Y is (a%(a-b)).

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_X
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/b) - 1. For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_X is (a/(a-b)) - 1.

fields.name: RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1
fields.desc: For b <= a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 0 . For b > a/2, the value of I2S_RX_CLKM_DIV_YN1 is 1.

fields.name: TX_CLKM_DIV_Y

1610649604.name: GPIO%s
1610649604.desc: IO MUX Configure Register for pad GPIO0

fields.name: MCU_OE
fields.desc: Output enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: output enabled; 0: output disabled.

fields.name: SLP_SEL
fields.desc: Sleep mode selection of this pad. Set to 1 to put the pad in pad mode.

fields.name: MCU_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad in sleep mode. 1: internal pull-down enabled; 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: MCU_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: internal pull-up enabled; 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: MCU_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad during sleep mode. 1: input enabled; 0: input disabled.

fields.name: FUN_WPD
fields.desc: Pull-down enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-down enabled; 0: internal pull-down disabled.

fields.name: FUN_WPU
fields.desc: Pull-up enable of the pad. 1: internal pull-up enabled; 0: internal pull-up disabled.

fields.name: FUN_IE
fields.desc: Input enable of the pad. 1: input enabled; 0: input disabled.

fields.name: FUN_DRV
fields.desc: Select the drive strength of the pad. 0: ~5 mA; 1: ~10mA; 2: ~20mA; 3: ~40mA.

fields.name: MCU_SEL
fields.desc: Select IO MUX function for this signal. 0: Select Function 1; 1: Select Function 2; etc.

fields.name: FILTER_EN
fields.desc: Enable filter for pin input signals. 1: Filter enabled; 2: Filter disabled.

fields.name: REG_DATE
fields.desc: Version control register

fields.name: LCD_CLKCNT_N
fields.desc:
f<SUB>LCD_PCLK</SUB>
 = f<SUB>LCD_CLK</SUB>/(LCD_CAM_LCD_CLKCNT_N + 1) when LCD_CAM_LCD_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK is 0. Note: this field must not be configured to 0.

fields.name: LCD_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc:
1: f<SUB>LCD_PCLK</SUB>
= f<SUB>LCD_CLK</SUB>. 0: f<SUB>LCD_PCLK</SUB>
 = f<SUB>LCD_CLK</SUB>/(LCD_CAM_LCD_CLKCNT_N + 1).

fields.name: LCD_CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: LCD_PCLK line is high in idle. 0: LCD_PCLK line is low in idle.

fields.name: LCD_CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: LCD_PCLK is high in the first half clock cycle. 0: LCD_PCLK is low in the first half clock cycle.

fields.name: LCD_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral LCD clock divider value.

fields.name: LCD_CLKM_DIV_B
fields.desc: Fractional clock divider numerator value.

fields.name: LCD_CLKM_DIV_A
fields.desc: Fractional clock divider denominator value.

fields.name: LCD_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: Select LCD module source clock. 0: clock source is disabled. 1: XTAL_CLK. 2: PLL_D2_CLK. 3: PLL_F160M_CLK.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to force enable the clock for all configuration registers. Clock gate is not used.

fields.name: CAM_STOP_EN
fields.desc: Camera stop enable signal, 1: camera stops when GDMA Rx FIFO is full. 0: Do not stop.

fields.name: CAM_VSYNC_FILTER_THRES
fields.desc: Filter threshold value for CAM_VSYNC signal.

fields.name: CAM_UPDATE
fields.desc: 1: Update camera registers. This bit is cleared by hardware. 0: Do not care.

fields.name: CAM_BYTE_ORDER
fields.desc: 1: Invert data byte order, only valid in 16-bit mode. 0: Do not change.

fields.name: CAM_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: 1: Change data bit order, change CAM_DATA_in[7:0] to CAM_DATA_in[0:7] in 8-bit mode, and bits[15:0] to bits[0:15] in 16-bit mode. 0: Do not change.

fields.name: CAM_LINE_INT_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable to generate LCD_CAM_CAM_HS_INT. 0: Disable.

fields.name: CAM_VS_EOF_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable CAM_VSYNC to generate in_suc_eof. 0: in_suc_eof is controlled by LCD_CAM_CAM_REC_DATA_BYTELEN.

fields.name: CAM_CLKM_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Integral camera clock divider value.

fields.name: CAM_CLKM_DIV_B
fields.desc: Fractional clock divider numerator value.

fields.name: CAM_CLKM_DIV_A
fields.desc: Fractional clock divider denominator value.

fields.name: CAM_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: Select camera module source clock. 0: Clock source is disabled. 1: XTAL_CLK. 2: PLL_D2_CLK. 3: PLL_F160M_CLK.

fields.name: CAM_REC_DATA_BYTELEN
fields.desc: Configure camera received data byte length. When the length of received data reaches this value + 1, GDMA in_suc_eof_int is triggered.

fields.name: CAM_LINE_INT_NUM
fields.desc: Configure line number. When the number of received lines reaches this value + 1, LCD_CAM_CAM_HS_INT is triggered.

fields.name: CAM_CLK_INV
fields.desc: 1: Invert the input signal CAM_PCLK. 0: Do not invert.

fields.name: CAM_VSYNC_FILTER_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable CAM_VSYNC filter function. 0: Bypass.

fields.name: CAM_2BYTE_EN
fields.desc: 1: The width of input data is 16 bits. 0: The width of input data is 8 bits.

fields.name: CAM_DE_INV

fields.name: CAM_CONV_YUV_MODE

fields.name: LCD_VBK_CYCLELEN

fields.name: LCD_CD_CMD_SET

fields.name: LC_DATE
fields.desc: Version control register

fields.name: TIMER_SEL
fields.desc:
This field is used to select one of timers for channel %s.

0: select timer0

1: select timer1

2: select timer2

3: select timer3

fields.name: SIG_OUT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable signal output on channel %s.

fields.name: IDLE_LV
fields.desc: This bit is used to control the output value when channel %s is inactive (when LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s is 0).

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: This bit is used to update LEDC_HPOINT_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_START_CH%s, LEDC_SIG_OUT_EN_CH%s, LEDC_TIMER_SEL_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_NUM_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_SCALE_CH%s, LEDC_DUTY_INC_CH%s, and LEDC_OVF_CNT_EN_CH%s fields for channel %s, and will be automatically cleared by hardware.

fields.name: OVF_NUM
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the maximum times of overflow minus 1.

The LEDC_OVF_CNT_CH%s_INT interrupt will be triggered when channel %s overflows for (LEDC_OVF_NUM_CH%s + 1) times.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the ovf_cnt of channel %s.

fields.name: OVF_CNT_RESET_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit of LEDC_OVF_CNT_RESET_CH%s.

fields.name: HPOINT
fields.desc: The output value changes to high when the selected timers has reached the value specified by this register.

fields.name: DUTY
fields.desc:
This register is used to change the output duty by controlling the Lpoint.

The output value turns to low when the selected timers has reached the Lpoint.

fields.name: DUTY_SCALE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the changing step scale of duty on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_CYCLE
fields.desc: The duty will change every LEDC_DUTY_CYCLE_CH%s on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to control the number of times the duty cycle will be changed.

fields.name: DUTY_INC
fields.desc: This register is used to increase or decrease the duty of output signal on channel %s. 1: Increase; 0: Decrease.

fields.name: DUTY_START
fields.desc: Other configured fields in LEDC_CH%s_CONF1_REG will start to take effect when this bit is set to 1.

fields.name: DUTY_R
fields.desc: This register stores the current duty of output signal on channel %s.

fields.name: DUTY_RES
fields.desc: This register is used to control the range of the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: CLK_DIV
fields.desc:
This register is used to configure the divisor for the divider in timer %s.

The least significant eight bits represent the fractional part.

fields.name: PAUSE
fields.desc: This bit is used to suspend the counter in timer %s.

fields.name: RST
fields.desc: This bit is used to reset timer %s. The counter will show 0 after reset.

fields.name: TICK_SEL
fields.desc:
This bit is used to select clock for timer %s. When this bit is set to 1 LEDC_APB_CLK_SEL[1:0] should be 1, otherwise the timer clock may be not accurate.

1'h0: SLOW_CLK 1'h1: REF_TICK

fields.name: PARA_UP
fields.desc: Set this bit to update LEDC_CLK_DIV_TIMER%s and LEDC_TIMER%s_DUTY_RES.

fields.name: CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the current counter value of timer %s.

fields.name: CH0_NEG_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a negative edge.

1: Increase the counter;2: Decrease the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH0_POS_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 0 detects a positive edge.

1: Increase the counter;2: Decrease the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH0_HCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification;1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase);2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH0_LCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification;1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase);2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH1_NEG_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a negative edge.

1: Increment the counter;2: Decrement the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_POS_MODE
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a positive edge.

1: Increment the counter;2: Decrement the counter;0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_HCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

fields.name: CH1_LCTRL_MODE
fields.desc:

0: No modification;1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase);2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: version

fields.name: CONTROLLER_RESET
fields.desc: To reset controller, firmware should set this bit. This bit is auto-cleared after two AHB and two sdhost_cclk_in clock cycles.

fields.name: FIFO_RESET
fields.desc:
To reset FIFO, firmware should set bit to 1. This bit is auto-cleared after completion of reset operation.
Note: FIFO pointers will be out of reset after 2 cycles of system clocks in addition to synchronization delay (2 cycles of card clock), after the fifo_reset is cleared.

fields.name: DMA_RESET
fields.desc: To reset DMA interface, firmware should set bit to 1. This bit is auto-cleared after two AHB clocks.

fields.name: INT_ENABLE
fields.desc: Global interrupt enable/disable bit. 0: Disable; 1: Enable.

fields.name: READ_WAIT
fields.desc: For sending read-wait to SDIO cards.

fields.name: SEND_IRQ_RESPONSE
fields.desc: Bit automatically clears once response is sent. To wait for MMC card interrupts, host issues CMD40 and waits for interrupt response from MMC card(s). In the meantime, if host wants SD/MMC to exit waiting for interrupt state, it can set this bit, at which time SD/MMC command state-machine sends CMD40 response on bus and returns to idle state.

fields.name: ABORT_READ_DATA
fields.desc: After a suspend-command is issued during a read-operation, software polls the card to find when the suspend-event occurred. Once the suspend-event has occurred, software sets the bit which will reset the data state machine that is waiting for the next block of data. This bit is automatically cleared once the data state machine is reset to idle.

fields.name: SEND_CCSD
fields.desc:
When set, SD/MMC sends CCSD to the CE-ATA device. Software sets this bit only if the current command is expecting CCS (that is, RW_BLK), and if interrupts are enabled for the CE-ATA device. Once the CCSD pattern is sent to the device, SD/MMC automatically clears the SDHOST_SEND_CCSD bit. It also sets the Command Done (CD) bit  in the SDHOST_RINTSTS_REG register, and generates an interrupt for the host, in case the Command Done interrupt is not masked. 
NOTE: Once the SDHOST_SEND_CCSD bit is set, it takes two card clock cycles to drive the CCSD on the CMD line. Due to this, within the boundary conditions the CCSD may be sent to the CE-ATA device, even if the device has signalled CCS.

fields.name: SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD
fields.desc: Always Set SDHOST_SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD and SDHOST_SEND_CCSD bits together; SDHOST_SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD should not be set independently of send_ccsd. When set, SD/MMC automatically sends an internally-generated STOP command (CMD12) to the CE-ATA device. After sending this internally-generated STOP command, the Auto Command Done (ACD) bit in SDHOST_RINTSTS_REG is set and an interrupt is generated for the host, in case the ACD interrupt is not masked. After sending the Command Completion Signal Disable (CCSD), SD/MMC automatically clears the  SDHOST_SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD bit.

fields.name: CEATA_DEVICE_INTERRUPT_STATUS
fields.desc: Software should appropriately write to this bit after the power-on reset or any other reset to the CE-ATA device. After reset, the CE-ATA device's interrupt is usually disabled (nIEN = 1). If the host enables the CE-ATA device's interrupt, then software should set this bit.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER0
fields.desc: Clock divider0 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER1
fields.desc: Clock divider1 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER2
fields.desc: Clock divider2 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER3
fields.desc: Clock divider3 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLKSRC
CCLK_ENABLE
LP_ENABLE

1610776596.name: TMOUT
1610776596.desc: Data and response timeout configuration register

fields.name: RESPONSE_TIMEOUT
fields.desc: Response timeout value. Value is specified in terms of number of card output clocks, i.e., sdhost_cclk_out.

fields.name: DATA_TIMEOUT
fields.desc:
Value for card data read timeout. This value is also used for data starvation by host timeout. The timeout counter is started only after the card clock is stopped. This value is specified in number of card output clocks, i.e. sdhost_cclk_out of the selected card.
NOTE: The software timer should be used if the timeout value is in the order of 100 ms. In this case, read data timeout interrupt needs to be disabled.

fields.name: CARD_WIDTH4
fields.desc:
One bit per card indicates if card is 1-bit or 4-bit mode.
0: 1-bit mode;
1: 4-bit mode.
Bit[1:0] correspond to card[1:0] respectively.

fields.name: CARD_WIDTH8
fields.desc:
One bit per card indicates if card is in 8-bit mode.
0: Non 8-bit mode;
1: 8-bit mode.
Bit[17:16] correspond to card[1:0] respectively.

1610776604.name: BLKSIZ
1610776604.desc: Card data block size configuration register

fields.name: BLOCK_SIZE
fields.desc: Block size.

fields.name: BYTE_COUNT
fields.desc: Number of bytes to be transferred, should be an integral multiple of Block Size for block transfers. For data transfers of undefined byte lengths, byte count should be set to 0. When byte count is set to 0, it is the responsibility of host to explicitly send stop/abort command to terminate data transfer.

fields.name: INT_MASK
SDIO_INT_MASK
fields.desc: SDIO interrupt mask, one bit for each card. Bit[17:16] correspond to card[15:0] respectively. When masked, SDIO interrupt detection for that card is disabled. 0 masks an interrupt, and 1 enables an interrupt.

fields.name: CMDARG
fields.desc: Value indicates command argument to be passed to the card.

fields.name: INDEX
fields.desc: Command index.

fields.name: RESPONSE_EXPECT
fields.desc: 0: No response expected from card; 1: Response expected from card.

fields.name: RESPONSE_LENGTH
fields.desc: 0: Short response expected from card; 1: Long response expected from card.

fields.name: CHECK_RESPONSE_CRC
fields.desc:
0: Do not check; 1: Check response CRC.
Some of command responses do not return valid CRC bits. Software should disable CRC checks for those commands in order to disable CRC checking by controller.

fields.name: DATA_EXPECTED
fields.desc: 0: No data transfer expected; 1: Data transfer expected.

fields.name: READ_WRITE
fields.desc:
0: Read from card; 1: Write to card.
Don't care if no data is expected from card.

fields.name: TRANSFER_MODE
fields.desc:
0: Block data transfer command; 1: Stream data transfer command.
Don't care if no data expected.

fields.name: SEND_AUTO_STOP
fields.desc: 0: No stop command is sent at the end of data transfer; 1: Send stop command at the end of data transfer.

fields.name: WAIT_PRVDATA_COMPLETE
fields.desc:
0: Send command at once, even if previous data transfer has not completed; 1: Wait for previous data transfer to complete before sending Command.
The SDHOST_WAIT_PRVDATA_COMPLETE] = 0 option is typically used to query status of card during data transfer or to stop current data transfer. SDHOST_CARD_NUMBERr should be same as in previous command.

fields.name: STOP_ABORT_CMD
fields.desc:
0: Neither stop nor abort command can stop current data transfer. If abort is sent to function-number currently selected or not in data-transfer mode, then bit should be set to 0; 1: Stop or abort command intended to stop current data transfer in progress.
When open-ended or predefined data transfer is in progress, and host issues stop or abort command to stop data transfer, bit should be set so that command/data state-machines of CIU can return correctly to idle state.

fields.name: SEND_INITIALIZATION
fields.desc:
0: Do not send initialization sequence (80 clocks of 1) before sending this command; 1: Send initialization sequence before sending this command.
After powered on, 80 clocks must be sent to card for initialization before sending any commands to card. Bit should be set while sending first command to card so that controller will initialize clocks before sending command to card.

fields.name: CARD_NUMBER
fields.desc: Card number in use. Represents physical slot number of card being accessed. In SD-only mode, up to two cards are supported.

fields.name: UPDATE_CLOCK_REGISTERS_ONLY
fields.desc:
0: Normal command sequence; 1: Do not send commands, just update clock register value into card clock domain.
Following register values are transferred into card clock domain: CLKDIV, CLRSRC, and CLKENA.
Changes card clocks (change frequency, truncate off or on, and set low-frequency mode). This is provided in order to change clock frequency or stop clock without having to send command to cards. During normal command sequence, when sdhost_update_clock_registers_only = 0, following control registers are transferred from BIU to CIU: CMD, CMDARG, TMOUT, CTYPE, BLKSIZ, and BYTCNT. CIU uses new register values for new command sequence to card(s). When bit is set, there are no Command Done interrupts because no command is sent to SD_MMC_CEATA cards.

fields.name: READ_CEATA_DEVICE
fields.desc:
Read access flag.
0: Host is not performing read access (RW_REG or RW_BLK)towards CE-ATA device;
1: Host is performing read access (RW_REG or RW_BLK) towards CE-ATA device.
Software should set this bit to indicate that CE-ATA device is being accessed for read transfer. This bit is used to disable read data timeout indication while performing CE-ATA read transfers. Maximum value of I/O transmission delay can be no less than 10 seconds. SD/MMC should not indicate read data timeout while waiting for data from CE-ATA device.

fields.name: CCS_EXPECTED
fields.desc:
Expected Command Completion Signal (CCS) configuration.
0: Interrupts are not enabled in CE-ATA device (nIEN = 1 in ATA control register), or command does not expect CCS from device;
1: Interrupts are enabled in CE-ATA device (nIEN = 0), and RW_BLK command expects command completion signal from CE-ATA device. 
If the command expects Command Completion Signal (CCS) from the CE-ATA device, the software should set this control bit. SD/MMC sets Data Transfer Over (DTO) bit in RINTSTS register and generates interrupt to host if Data Transfer Over interrupt is not masked.

If a write is attempted, hardware lock error is set in raw interrupt register. Once command is sent and a response is received from SD_MMC_CEATA cards, Command Done bit is set in the raw interrupt Register.

fields.name: FIFO_COUNT
fields.desc: FIFO count, number of filled locations in FIFO.

fields.name: TX_WMARK
fields.desc: FIFO threshold watermark level when transmitting data to card. When FIFO data count is less than or equal to this number, DMA/FIFO request is raised. If Interrupt is enabled, then interrupt  occurs. During end of packet, request or interrupt is generated, regardless of threshold programming.In non-DMA mode, when transmit FIFO threshold (TXDR) interrupt is enabled, then interrupt is generated instead of DMA request. During end of packet, on last interrupt, host is responsible for filling FIFO with only required remaining bytes (not before FIFO is full or after CIU completes data transfers, because FIFO may not be empty).  In DMA mode, at end of packet, if last transfer is less than burst  size, DMA controller does single cycles until required bytes are  transferred.

fields.name: RX_WMARK
fields.desc: FIFO threshold watermark level when receiving data to card.When FIFO data count reaches greater than this number , DMA/FIFO request is raised. During end of packet, request is generated regardless of threshold programming in order to complete any remaining data.In non-DMA mode, when receiver FIFO threshold (RXDR) interrupt is enabled, then interrupt is generated instead of DMA request.During end of packet, interrupt is not generated if threshold programming is larger than any remaining data. It is responsibility of host to read remaining bytes on seeing Data Transfer Done interrupt.In DMA mode, at end of packet, even if remaining bytes are less than threshold, DMA request does single transfers to flush out any remaining bytes before Data Transfer Done interrupt is set.

fields.desc:
Hardware reset.
1: Active mode; 
0: Reset. 
These bits cause the cards to enter pre-idle state, which requires them to be re-initialized. SDHOST_RST_CARD_RESET[0] should be set to 1'b0 to reset card0, SDHOST_RST_CARD_RESET[1] should be set to 1'b0 to reset card1.

fields.name: SWR
fields.desc: Software Reset. When set, the DMA Controller resets all its internal registers. It is automatically cleared after one clock cycle.

fields.name: FB
fields.desc: Fixed Burst. Controls whether the AHB Master interface performs fixed burst transfers or not. When set, the AHB will use only SINGLE, INCR4, INCR8 or INCR16 during start of normal burst transfers. When reset, the AHB will use SINGLE and INCR burst transfer operations.

fields.name: DE
fields.desc: IDMAC Enable. When set, the IDMAC is enabled.

fields.name: PBL
PD
fields.desc: Poll Demand. If the OWNER bit of a descriptor is not set, the FSM goes to the Suspend state. The host needs to write any value into this register for the IDMAC FSM to resume normal descriptor fetch operation. This is a write only .

fields.name: DBADDR
fields.desc: Start of Descriptor List. Contains the base address of the First Descriptor. The LSB bits [1:0] are ignored and taken as all-zero by the IDMAC internally. Hence these LSB bits may be treated as read-only.

fields.name: TI
fields.desc: Transmit Interrupt. Indicates that data transmission is finished for a descriptor. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: RI
fields.desc: Receive Interrupt. Indicates the completion of data reception for a descriptor. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: FBE
fields.desc: Fatal Bus Error Interrupt. Indicates that a Bus Error occurred (IDSTS[12:10]) . When this bit is set, the DMA disables all its bus accesses. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: DU
fields.desc: Descriptor Unavailable Interrupt. This bit is set when the descriptor is unavailable due to OWNER bit = 0 (DES0[31] = 0). Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: CES
NIS
fields.desc: Normal Interrupt Summary. Logical OR of the following: IDSTS[0] : Transmit Interrupt, IDSTS[1] : Receive Interrupt. Only unmasked bits affect this bit. This is a sticky bit and must be cleared each time a corresponding bit that causes NIS to be set is cleared. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: AIS
fields.desc: Abnormal Interrupt Summary. Logical OR of the following: IDSTS[2] : Fatal Bus Interrupt, IDSTS[4] : DU bit Interrupt. Only unmasked bits affect this bit. This is a sticky bit and must be cleared each time a corresponding bit that causes AIS to be set is cleared. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: FBE_CODE
FSM
TI
fields.desc: Transmit Interrupt Enable. When set with Normal Interrupt Summary Enable, Transmit Interrupt is enabled. When reset, Transmit Interrupt is disabled.

fields.name: RI
fields.desc: Receive Interrupt Enable. When set with Normal Interrupt Summary Enable, Receive Interrupt is enabled. When reset, Receive Interrupt is disabled.

fields.name: FBE
fields.desc: Fatal Bus Error Enable. When set with Abnormal Interrupt Summary Enable, the Fatal Bus Error Interrupt is enabled. When reset, Fatal Bus Error Enable Interrupt is disabled.

fields.name: DU
fields.desc: Descriptor Unavailable Interrupt. When set along with Abnormal Interrupt Summary Enable, the DU interrupt is enabled.

fields.name: CES

fields.name: EDMA_BOUNDARY_LOCK
fields.desc: Set 1 to lock EDMA boundary registers.

fields.name: EDMA_BOUNDARY_0
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the boundary 0 of external RAM. The unit is 4K. For example, set this field to 0x80, then the address boundary 0 would be 0x3C080000 (0x3C000000 + 0x80 * 4K).

fields.name: EDMA_BOUNDARY_1
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the boundary 1 of external RAM. The unit is 4K. For example, set this field to 0x80, then the address boundary 0 would be 0x3C080000 (0x3C000000 + 0x80 * 4K).

fields.name: EDMA_BOUNDARY_2
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the boundary 2 of external RAM. The unit is 4K. For example, set this field to 0x80, then the address boundary 0 would be 0x3C080000 (0x3C000000 + 0x80 * 4K).

fields.name: EDMA_PMS_SPI2_LOCK
fields.desc: Set 1 to lock EDMA-SPI2 permission control registers.

fields.name: ATTR1
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of SPI2 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 0 and less than boundary 1, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: ATTR2
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of SPI2 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 1 and less than boundary 2, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: EDMA_PMS_SPI3_LOCK
fields.desc: Set 1 to lock EDMA-SPI3 permission control registers.

fields.name: ATTR1
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of SPI3 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 0 and less than boundary 1, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: ATTR2
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of SPI3 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 1 and less than boundary 2, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: EDMA_PMS_UHCI0_LOCK
fields.desc: Set 1 to lock EDMA-UHCI0 permission control registers.

fields.name: ATTR1
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of UHCI0 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 0 and less than boundary 1, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: ATTR2
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of UHCI0 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 1 and less than boundary 2, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: ATTR1
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of I2S0 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 0 and less than boundary 1, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: ATTR2
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of I2S0 accessing address, which is larger than boundary 1 and less than boundary 2, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: ATTR2
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of LCD/CAM accessing address, which is larger than boundary 1 and less than boundary 2, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: EDMA_PMS_AES_LOCK

fields.name: ATTR1

fields.name: EDMA_PMS_ADC_DAC_LOCK

fields.name: ATTR1
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of ADC/DAC accessing address, which is larger than boundary 0 and less than boundary 1, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.name: ATTR2
fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of ADC/DAC accessing address, which is larger than boundary 1 and less than boundary 2, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of RMT accessing address, which is larger than boundary 0 and less than boundary 1, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

fields.desc: This field is used to configure the permission of RMT accessing address, which is larger than boundary 1 and less than boundary 2, through EDMA. Bit 0: set this bit to enable read permission. Bit 1: set this bit to enable write permission.

1611404040.name: CLOCK_GATE
1611404040.desc: Sensitive module clock gate configuration register.

fields.name: REG_CLK_EN
fields.desc: Set 1 to enable clock gate function.

fields.name: DIS_RTC_CPU
fields.desc: Set 1 to disable rtc coprocessor.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Sensitive Date register.

fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: sha mode

fields.name: T_STRING
fields.desc: sha t_string(used if and only if mode == sha_256/t)

fields.name: T_LENGTH
fields.desc: sha t_length(used if and only if mode == sha_256/t)

fields.name: DMA_BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: dma-sha block number

fields.name: START
fields.desc: reserved.

fields.name: CONTINUE
fields.desc: reserved.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: sha busy state. 1'b0: idle 1'b1: busy

fields.name: DMA_START
fields.desc: start dma-sha

fields.name: DMA_CONTINUE
fields.desc: continue dma-sha

fields.name: CLEAR_INTERRUPT
fields.desc: clear sha interrupt

fields.name: INTERRUPT_ENA
fields.desc: sha interrupt enable register. 1'b0: disable(default) 1'b1: enable

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: sha date information/ sha version information

1610854464.name: H_MEM[%s]
1610854464.desc: Sha H memory which contains intermediate hash or finial hash.

1610854528.name: M_MEM[%s]
1610854528.desc: Sha M memory which contains message.

fields.name: FDUMMY_OUT
fields.desc: In the DUMMY phase the signal level of SPI bus is output by the SPI0 controller.

fields.name: FDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in DOUT phase.

fields.name: FDIN_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in DIN phase.

fields.name: FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in ADDR phase.

fields.name: FCMD_DUAL
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 2-bit-mode(2-bm) in CMD phase.

fields.name: FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 4-bit-mode(4-bm) in CMD phase.

fields.name: FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in CMD phase.

fields.name: FASTRD_MODE
fields.desc: This bit should be set when SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD or SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL is set.

fields.name: FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In hardware 0x3B read operation, DIN phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In hardware 0x6B read operation, DIN phase apply 4 signals(4-bit-mode). 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.

fields.name: FREAD_DIO
fields.desc: In hardware 0xBB read operation, ADDR phase and DIN phase apply 2 signals(2-bit-mode). 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FREAD_QIO
fields.desc: In hardware 0xEB read operation, ADDR phase and DIN phase apply 4 signals(4-bit-mode). 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: CLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI Bus clock (SPI_CLK) mode bits. 0: SPI Bus clock (SPI_CLK) is off when CS inactive 1: SPI_CLK is delayed one cycle after SPI_CS inactive 2: SPI_CLK is delayed two cycles after SPI_CS inactive 3: SPI_CLK is always on.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: SPI0 RX FIFO reset signal. Set this bit and clear it before SPI0 transfer starts.

fields.name: CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles-1) of PREP phase by SPI_CLK, which is the SPI_CS setup time. These bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP bit.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI Bus CS (SPI_CS) signal is delayed to inactive by SPI Bus clock (SPI_CLK), which is the SPI_CS hold time in non-ECC mode. These bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD bit.

fields.name: ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME + SPI_MEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME is the SPI_CS hold cycle in ECC mode when accessed flash.

fields.name: ECC_SKIP_PAGE_CORNER
fields.desc: 1: MSPI skips page corner when accesses flash. 0: Not skip page corner when accesses flash.

fields.name: ECC_16TO18_BYTE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable MSPI ECC 16 bytes data with 2 ECC bytes mode when accesses flash.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: These bits are used to set the minimum CS high time tSHSL between SPI burst transfer when accesses to flash. tSHSL is (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY[5:0] + 1) MSPI core clock cycles.

fields.name: SYNC_RESET
fields.desc: The FSM will be reset.

1610625044.name: CLOCK
1610625044.desc: SPI_CLK clock division register when SPI0 accesses to flash.

fields.name: CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: It must equal to the value of SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N.

fields.name: CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: It must be a floor value of ((SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses flash, f_SPI_CLK = f_MSPI_CORE_CLK/(SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N+1)

fields.name: CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses flash, set this bit in 1-division mode, f_SPI_CLK = f_MSPI_CORE_CLK.

fields.name: CS_HOLD
fields.desc: Set this bit to keep SPI_CS low when MSPI is in DONE state.

fields.name: CS_SETUP
fields.desc: Set this bit to keep SPI_CS low when MSPI is in PREP state.

fields.name: CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: This bit, combined with SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE bit, is used to change the clock mode 0~3 of SPI_CLK.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: SPI_CLK is disabled(No clock edges) in DUMMY phase when the bit is enable.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the DUMMY phase of an SPI transfer.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The SPI_CLK cycle length minus 1 of DUMMY phase.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of ADDR phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of user defined(USR) command.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of CMD phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

fields.name: WB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode  it is combined with SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE bit.

fields.name: EXT_ADDR
fields.desc: The register are the higher 32bits in the 64 bits address mode.

fields.name: FSUB_PIN
fields.desc: Flash is connected to SPI SUBPIN bus.

fields.name: SSUB_PIN
fields.desc: Ext_RAM is connected to SPI SUBPIN bus.

fields.name: CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: SPI_CLK line is high when idle. 0: SPI_CLK line is low when idle

fields.name: CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: SPI_CS line keep low when the bit is set.

1610625084.name: CACHE_FCTRL
1610625084.desc: SPI0 external RAM bit mode control register.

fields.name: CACHE_REQ_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable Cache's access and SPI0's transfer.

fields.name: CACHE_USR_CMD_4BYTE
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 read flash with 32 bits address. The value of SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN should be 31.

fields.name: CACHE_FLASH_USR_CMD
fields.desc: 1: The command value of SPI0 reads flash is SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_VALUE. 0: Hardware read command value, controlled by SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD, SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL and SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE bits.

fields.name: FDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to flash, set this bit to enable 2-bm in DIN phase.

fields.name: FDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to flash, set this bit to enable 2-bm in DOUT phase.

fields.name: FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to flash, set this bit to enable 2-bm in ADDR phase.

fields.name: FDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to flash, set this bit to enable 4-bm in DIN phase.

fields.name: FDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to flash, set this bit to enable 4-bm in DOUT phase.

fields.name: FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to flash, set this bit to enable 4-bm in ADDR phase.

fields.name: CACHE_USR_SCMD_4BYTE
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 read Ext_RAM with 32 bits address. The value of SPI_MEM_SRAM_ADDR_BITLEN should be 31.

fields.name: USR_SRAM_DIO
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable 2-bm in all the phases of SPI0 Ext_RAM transfer.

fields.name: USR_SRAM_QIO
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable QPI mode in all SPI0 Ext_RAM transfer.

fields.name: USR_WR_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable DUMMY phase in write operations.

fields.name: USR_RD_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable DUMMY phase in read operations.

fields.name: CACHE_SRAM_USR_RCMD
fields.desc: 1: The command value of SPI0 read Ext_RAM is SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WR_CMD_VALUE. 0: The value is 0x2.

fields.name: SRAM_RDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, it is the SPI_CLK cycles minus 1 of DUMMY phase in read data transfer.

fields.name: SRAM_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, it is the length in bits of ADDR phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: CACHE_SRAM_USR_WCMD
fields.desc: 1: The command value of SPI0 write Ext_RAM is SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RD_CMD_VALUE. 0: The value is 0x3.

fields.name: SRAM_OCT
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable OPI mode in all SPI0 Ext_RAM transfer.

fields.name: SRAM_WDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, it is the SPI_CLK cycles minus 1 of DUMMY phase in write data transfer.

1610625092.name: SRAM_CMD
1610625092.desc: SPI0 external RAM mode control register

fields.name: SCLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_CLK mode bits  when SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM. 0: SPI_CLK is off when CS inactive 1: SPI_CLK is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI_CLK is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI_CLK is always on.

fields.name: SWB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits when SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM.

fields.name: SDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 2-bm in DIN phase.

fields.name: SDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 2-bm in DOUT phase.

fields.name: SADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 2-bm in ADDR phase.

fields.name: SCMD_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 2-bm in CMD phase.

fields.name: SDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 4-bm in DIN phase.

fields.name: SDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 4-bm in DOUT phase.

fields.name: SADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 4-bm in ADDR phase.

fields.name: SCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 4-bm in CMD phase.

fields.name: SDIN_OCT
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 8-bm in DIN phase.

fields.name: SDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 8-bm in DOUT phase.

fields.name: SADDR_OCT
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 8-bm in ADDR phase.

fields.name: SCMD_OCT
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 8-bm in CMD phase.

fields.name: SDUMMY_OUT
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, in the DUMMY phase the signal level of SPI bus is output by the SPI0 controller.

1610625096.name: SRAM_DRD_CMD
1610625096.desc: SPI0 external RAM DDR read command control register

fields.name: CACHE_SRAM_USR_RD_CMD_VALUE
fields.desc: When SPI0 reads Ext_RAM, it is the command value of CMD phase.

fields.name: CACHE_SRAM_USR_RD_CMD_BITLEN
fields.desc: When SPI0 reads Ext_RAM, it is the length in bits of CMD phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1610625100.name: SRAM_DWR_CMD
1610625100.desc: SPI0 external RAM DDR write command control register

fields.name: CACHE_SRAM_USR_WR_CMD_VALUE
fields.desc: When SPI0 writes Ext_RAM, it is the command value of CMD phase.

fields.name: CACHE_SRAM_USR_WR_CMD_BITLEN
fields.desc: When SPI0 writes Ext_RAM, it is the length in bits of CMD phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1610625104.name: SRAM_CLK
1610625104.desc: SPI_CLK clock division register when SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM.

fields.name: SCLKCNT_L
fields.desc: It must equal to the value of SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_N.

fields.name: SCLKCNT_H
fields.desc: It must be a floor value of ((SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: SCLKCNT_N
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, f_SPI_CLK = f_MSPI_CORE_CLK/(SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_N+1)

fields.name: SCLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: When SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM, set this bit in 1-division mode, f_SPI_CLK = f_MSPI_CORE_CLK.

fields.name: ST
fields.desc: The status of SPI0 state machine. 0: idle state(IDLE), 1: preparation state(PREP), 2: send command state(CMD), 3: send address state(ADDR), 4: red data state(DIN), 5:write data state(DOUT), 6: wait state(DUMMY), 7: done state(DONE).

1610625192.name: TIMING_CALI
1610625192.desc: SPI0 timing compensation register when accesses to flash.

fields.name: TIMING_CLK_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to power on HCLK. When PLL is powered on, the frequency of HCLK equals to that of PLL. Otherwise, the frequency equals to that of XTAL.

fields.name: TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: Set this bit to add extra SPI_CLK cycles in DUMMY phase for all reading operations.

fields.name: EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: Extra SPI_CLK cycles added in DUMMY phase for timing compensation, when SPI0 accesses to flash. Active when SPI_MEM_TIMING_CALI bit is set.

1610625196.name: DIN_MODE
1610625196.desc: MSPI input timing delay mode control register when accesses to flash.

fields.name: DIN0_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_D input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DIN1_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_Q input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DIN2_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_WP input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DIN3_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_HD input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DIN4_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO4 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DIN5_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO5 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DIN6_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO6 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DIN7_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO7 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: DINS_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_DQS input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_MEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

1610625200.name: DIN_NUM
1610625200.desc: MSPI input timing delay number control register when accesses to flash.

fields.name: DIN0_NUM
fields.desc: SPI_D input delay number.

fields.name: DIN1_NUM
fields.desc: SPI_Q input delay number.

fields.name: DIN2_NUM
fields.desc: SPI_WP input delay number.

fields.name: DIN3_NUM
fields.desc: SPI_HD input delay number.

fields.name: DIN4_NUM
fields.desc: SPI_IO4 input delay number.

fields.name: DIN5_NUM
fields.desc: SPI_IO5 input delay number.

fields.name: DIN6_NUM
fields.desc: SPI_IO6 input delay number.

fields.name: DIN7_NUM

fields.name: DOUT1_MODE

fields.name: DOUT2_MODE

fields.name: DOUT5_MODE

fields.name: DOUT6_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO6 output delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_TIMING_CLK_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to power on HCLK. When PLL is powered on, the frequency of HCLK equals to that of PLL. Otherwise, the frequency equals to that of XTAL.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: Set this bit to add extra SPI_CLK cycles in DUMMY phase for all reading operations.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: Extra SPI_CLK cycles added in DUMMY phase for timing compensation, when SPI0 accesses to Ext_RAM. Active when SPI_SMEM_TIMING_CALI bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN0_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_D input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN0_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN1_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_Q input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN3_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN2_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_WP input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN6_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN3_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_HD input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN9_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN4_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO4 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN12_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN5_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO5 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN15_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN6_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO6 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN18_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DIN7_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_IO7 input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DIN21_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DINS_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_DQS input delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 2: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 3: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK positive edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge. 4: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK positive edge. 5: Delay for (SPI_SMEM_DINS_NUM+1) cycles at HCLK negative edge and one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DOUT0_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_D output delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DOUT1_MODE
fields.desc: SPI_Q output delay mode. 0: No delay. 1: Delay one cycle at MSPI_CORE_CLK negative edge.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DOUT2_MODE
