fields.name: ECC_ERR_INT_NUM
fields.desc: Set the error times of MSPI ECC read to generate MSPI SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to calculate the error times of MSPI ECC read when accesses to flash.

fields.name: ECC_ERR_ADDR
fields.desc: These bits show the first MSPI ECC error address when SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN/SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set and accessed to flash/Ext_RAM, including ECC byte error and data error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit is set.

fields.name: ECC_DATA_ERR_BIT
fields.desc: It records the first ECC data error bit number when SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN/SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set and accessed to flash/Ext_RAM. The value ranges from 0~127, corresponding to the bit number in 16 data bytes. It is cleared by SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit.

fields.name: ECC_CHK_ERR_BIT
fields.desc: When SPI_MEM_ECC_BYTE_ERR is set, these bits show the error bit number of ECC byte.

fields.name: ECC_BYTE_ERR
fields.desc: It records the first ECC byte error when SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN/SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set and accessed to flash/Ext_RAM. It is cleared by SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit.

fields.name: ECC_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: This bits show the error times of MSPI ECC read, including ECC byte error and data byte error. It is cleared by when  SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR bit is set.

1610625244.name: SPI_SMEM_AC
1610625244.desc: MSPI external RAM ECC and SPI CS timing control register

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_SETUP
fields.desc: Set this bit to keep SPI_CS low when MSPI is in PREP state.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD
fields.desc: Set this bit to keep SPI_CS low when MSPI is in DONE state.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles-1) of PREP phase by SPI_CLK, which is the SPI_CS setup time. These bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP bit.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI Bus CS (SPI_CS) signal is delayed to inactive by SPI Bus clock (SPI_CLK), which is the SPI_CS hold time in non-ECC mode. These bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD bit.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_TIME + SPI_SMEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME is the MSPI CS hold cycles in ECC mode when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_SKIP_PAGE_CORNER
fields.desc: 1: MSPI skips page corner when accesses to external RAM. 0: Not skip page corner when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_16TO18_BYTE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable MSPI ECC 16 bytes data with 2 ECC bytes mode when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to calculate the error times of MSPI ECC read when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: These bits are used to set the minimum CS high time tSHSL between SPI burst transfer when accesses to external RAM. tSHSL is (SPI_SMEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY[5:0] + 1) MSPI core clock cycles.

1610625248.name: DDR
1610625248.desc: SPI0 flash DDR mode control register

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_EN
fields.desc: 1: in ddr mode,  0 in sdr mode

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_VAR_DUMMY
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable variable dummy cycle in DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_RDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder RX data of the word in DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_WDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to swap TX data of a word in DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_CMD_DIS
fields.desc: the bit is used to disable dual edge in CMD phase when ddr mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OUTMINBYTELEN
fields.desc: It is the minimum output data length in the panda device.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_TX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in MSPI ECC DDR write mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_RX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in MSPI ECC DDR read mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_USR_DDR_DQS_THD
fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI_CLK.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP
fields.desc: 1: Use internal signal  as data strobe, the strobe can not be delayed by input timing module. 0: Use input SPI_DQS signal from PAD as data strobe, the strobe can be delayed by input timing module

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP_MODE
fields.desc: When SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP and SPI_FMEM_DDR_EN are set, 1: Use internal SPI_CLK  as data strobe. 0: Use internal ~SPI_CLK  as data strobe. Otherwise this bit is not active.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the SPI HyperBus mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses to flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to flash. .

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.

1610625252.name: SPI_SMEM_DDR
1610625252.desc: SPI0 external RAM DDR mode control register

fields.name: EN
fields.desc: 1: in ddr mode,  0 in sdr mode

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_VAR_DUMMY
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable variable dummy cycle in spi ddr mode.

fields.name: RDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder rx data of the word in spi ddr mode.

fields.name: WDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder tx data of the word in spi ddr mode.

fields.name: CMD_DIS
fields.desc: the bit is used to disable dual edge in CMD phase when ddr mode.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_OUTMINBYTELEN
fields.desc: It is the minimum output data length in the ddr psram.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_TX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in MSPI ECC DDR write mode, when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_RX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in MSPI ECC DDR read mode, when accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_USR_DDR_DQS_THD
fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI_CLK.

fields.name: DQS_LOOP
fields.desc: 1: Use internal signal  as data strobe, the strobe can not be delayed by input timing module. 0: Use input SPI_DQS signal from PAD as data strobe, the strobe can be delayed by input timing module

fields.name: DQS_LOOP_MODE
fields.desc: When SPI_SMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP and SPI_SMEM_DDR_EN are set, 1: Use internal SPI_CLK  as data strobe. 0: Use internal ~SPI_CLK  as data strobe. Otherwise this bit is not active.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_HYPERBUS_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the SPI HyperBus mode.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses to flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to external RAM. .

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to external RAM, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to external RAM, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Register clock gate enable signal. 1: Enable. 0: Disable.

fields.name: CORE_CLK_SEL
fields.desc: When the digital system clock selects PLL clock and the frequency of PLL clock is 480MHz, the value of SPI_MEM_CORE_CLK_SEL:  0: SPI0/1 module clock (MSPI_CORE_CLK) is 80MHz. 1: MSPI_CORE_CLK is 120MHz.  2: MSPI_CORE_CLK is 160MHz. 3: MSPI_CORE_CLK is 240MHz. When the digital system clock selects PLL clock and the frequency of PLL clock is 320MHz, the value of SPI_MEM_CORE_CLK_SEL:  0: MSPI_CORE_CLK is 80MHz. 1: MSPI_CORE_CLK is 80MHz.  2: MSPI_CORE_CLK 160MHz. 3: Not used.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: ECC_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: ECC_ERR_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt. SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR and SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_CNT will be cleared by the pulse of this bit.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when SPI1 transfer is done and flash is already idle. When WRSR/PP/SE/BE/CE is sent and PES/PER command is sent, this bit is set when WRSR/PP/SE/BE/CE is success.  0: Others.

fields.name: ECC_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt. When APB_CTRL_FECC_ERR_INT_EN is set and  APB_CTRL_SECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read flash are equal or bigger than APB_CTRL_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When APB_CTRL_FECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared and  APB_CTRL_SECC_ERR_INT_EN is set, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM are equal or bigger than APB_CTRL_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When APB_CTRL_FECC_ERR_INT_EN and  APB_CTRL_SECC_ERR_INT_EN are set, this bit is triggered when the total error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM and flash are equal or bigger than APB_CTRL_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When APB_CTRL_FECC_ERR_INT_EN and  APB_CTRL_SECC_ERR_INT_EN are cleared, this bit will not be triggered.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: ECC_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_SPICLK_FUN_DRV
fields.desc: The driver of SPI_CLK PAD  is controlled by the bits SPI_SMEM_SPICLK_FUN_DRV[1:0] when the bit SPI_SPICLK_PAD_DRV_CTL_EN is set and MSPI accesses to external RAM.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_SPICLK_FUN_DRV
fields.desc: The driver of SPI_CLK PAD  is controlled by the bits SPI_FMEM_SPICLK_FUN_DRV[1:0] when the bit SPI_SPICLK_PAD_DRV_CTL_EN is set and MSPI accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_SPICLK_PAD_DRV_CTL_EN
fields.desc: SPI_CLK PAD driver control signal. 1: The driver of SPI_CLK PAD  is controlled by the bits SPI_FMEM_SPICLK_FUN_DRV[1:0] and SPI_SMEM_SPICLK_FUN_DRV[1:0]. 0: The driver of SPI_CLK PAD  is controlled by the bits IO_MUX_FUNC_DRV[1:0] of SPICLK PAD.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: SPI register version.

fields.name: FLASH_PE
fields.desc: In user mode, it is set to indicate that program/erase operation will be triggered. The bit is combined with SPI_MEM_USR bit. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR
fields.desc: User define command enable.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_HPM
fields.desc: Drive Flash into high performance mode.  The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_RES
fields.desc: This bit combined with SPI_MEM_RESANDRES bit releases Flash from the power-down state or high performance mode and obtains the devices ID. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_DP
fields.desc: Drive Flash into power down.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_CE
fields.desc: Chip erase enable. Chip erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_BE
fields.desc: Block erase enable(32KB) .  Block erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_SE
fields.desc: Sector erase enable(4KB). Sector erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_PP
fields.desc: Page program enable(1 byte ~64 bytes data to be programmed). Page program operation  will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done .1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_WRSR
fields.desc: Write status register enable.   Write status operation  will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_RDSR
fields.desc: Read status register-1.  Read status operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_RDID
fields.desc: Read JEDEC ID . Read ID command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_WRDI
fields.desc: Write flash disable. Write disable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_WREN
fields.desc: Write flash enable.  Write enable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_READ
fields.desc: Read flash enable. Read flash operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_VALUE
fields.desc: In user mode, it is the memory address. other then the bit0-bit23 is the memory address, the bit24-bit31 are the byte length of a transfer.

fields.name: FDUMMY_OUT
fields.desc: In the DUMMY phase the signal level of SPI bus is output by the SPI0 controller.

fields.name: FDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in DOUT phase.

fields.name: FDIN_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in DIN phase.

fields.name: FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in ADDR phase.

fields.name: FCMD_DUAL
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 2-bit-mode(2-bm) in CMD phase.

fields.name: FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 4-bit-mode(4-bm) in CMD phase.

fields.name: FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 8-bit-mode(8-bm) in CMD phase.

fields.name: FCS_CRC_EN
fields.desc: For SPI1,  initialize crc32 module before writing encrypted data to flash. Active low.

fields.name: TX_CRC_EN
fields.desc: For SPI1,  enable crc32 when writing encrypted data to flash. 1: enable 0:disable

fields.name: FASTRD_MODE
fields.desc: This bit should be set when SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD or SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL is set.

fields.name: FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In hardware 0x3B read operation, DIN phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: RESANDRES
fields.desc: The Device ID is read out to SPI_MEM_RD_STATUS register,  this bit combine with spi_mem_flash_res bit. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In hardware 0x6B read operation, DIN phase apply 4 signals(4-bit-mode). 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.

fields.name: WRSR_2B
fields.desc: Two bytes data will be written to status register when it is set. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FREAD_DIO
fields.desc: In hardware 0xBB read operation, ADDR phase and DIN phase apply 2 signals(2-bit-mode). 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FREAD_QIO
fields.desc: In hardware 0xEB read operation, ADDR phase and DIN phase apply 4 signals(4-bit-mode). 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: CLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI Bus clock (SPI_CLK) mode bits. 0: SPI Bus clock (SPI_CLK) is off when CS inactive 1: SPI_CLK is delayed one cycle after SPI_CS inactive 2: SPI_CLK is delayed two cycles after SPI_CS inactive 3: SPI_CLK is always on.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_DLY_RES
fields.desc: After RES/DP/HPM/PES/PER command is sent, SPI1 may waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4 or * 256) SPI_CLK cycles.

fields.name: SYNC_RESET
fields.desc: The FSM will be reset.

1610620948.name: CLOCK
1610620948.desc: SPI_CLK clock division register when SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM.

fields.name: CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: It must equal to the value of SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N.

fields.name: CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: It must be a floor value of ((SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: When SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM, f_SPI_CLK = f_MSPI_CORE_CLK/(SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N+1)

fields.name: CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: When SPI1 access to flash or Ext_RAM, set this bit in 1-division mode, f_SPI_CLK = f_MSPI_CORE_CLK.

fields.name: CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: This bit, combined with SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE bit, is used to change the clock mode 0~3 of SPI_CLK.

fields.name: FWRITE_DUAL
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 2-bm in DOUT phase in SPI1 write operation.

fields.name: FWRITE_QUAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 4-bm in DOUT phase in SPI1 write operation.

fields.name: FWRITE_DIO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 2-bm in ADDR and DOUT phase in SPI1 write operation.

fields.name: FWRITE_QIO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable 4-bit-mode(4-bm) in ADDR and DOUT phase in SPI1 write operation.

fields.name: USR_MISO_HIGHPART
fields.desc: DIN phase only access to high-part of the buffer SPI_MEM_W8_REG~SPI_MEM_W15_REG. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
fields.desc: DOUT phase only access to high-part of the buffer SPI_MEM_W8_REG~SPI_MEM_W15_REG. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: SPI_CLK is disabled(No clock edges) in DUMMY phase when the bit is enable.

fields.name: USR_MOSI
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the DOUT phase of an write-data operation.

fields.name: USR_MISO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable enable the DIN phase of a read-data operation.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable enable the DUMMY phase of an operation.

fields.name: USR_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable enable the ADDR phase of an operation.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable enable the CMD phase of an operation.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The SPI_CLK cycle length minus 1 of DUMMY phase.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of ADDR phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of user defined(USR) command.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of CMD phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

fields.name: USR_MOSI_DBITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of DOUT phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: USR_MISO_DBITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of DIN phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: STATUS
fields.desc: The value is stored when set SPI_MEM_FLASH_RDSR bit and SPI_MEM_FLASH_RES bit.

fields.name: WB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode  it is combined with SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE bit.

fields.name: EXT_ADDR
fields.desc: The register are the higher 32bits in the 64 bits address mode.

fields.name: CS0_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to raise high SPI_CS pin, which means that the SPI device(flash) connected to SPI_CS is in low level when SPI1 transfer starts.

fields.name: CS1_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to raise high SPI_CS1 pin, which means that the SPI device(Ext_RAM) connected to SPI_CS1 is in low level when SPI1 transfer starts.

fields.name: CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: SPI_CLK line is high when MSPI is idle. 0: SPI_CLK line is low when MSPI is idle.

fields.name: CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: SPI_CS line keep low when the bit is set.

fields.name: AUTO_PER
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable auto PER function. Hardware will sent out PER command if PES command is sent.

fields.name: DATA
fields.desc: For SPI1, the value of crc32.

fields.name: CACHE_USR_CMD_4BYTE
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI1 transfer with 32 bits address. The value of SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN should be 31.

fields.name: FDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 2-bm in DIN phase.

fields.name: FDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 2-bm in DOUT phase.

fields.name: FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: When SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 2-bm in ADDR phase.

fields.name: FDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 4-bm in DIN phase.

fields.name: FDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 4-bm in DOUT phase.

fields.name: FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: When SPI1 accesses to flash or Ext_RAM, set this bit to enable 4-bm in ADDR phase.

fields.name: ST
fields.desc: The status of SPI1 state machine. 0: idle state(IDLE), 1: preparation state(PREP), 2: send command state(CMD), 3: send address state(ADDR), 4: red data state(DIN), 5:write data state(DOUT), 6: wait state(DUMMY), 7: done state(DONE).

fields.name: BUF0
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF1
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF2
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF3
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF4
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF5
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF6
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF7
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF8
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF9
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF10
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF11
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF12
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF13
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF14
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: BUF15
fields.desc: data buffer

fields.name: WAITI_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable auto-waiting flash idle operation when PP/SE/BE/CE/WRSR/PES command is sent.

fields.name: WAITI_DUMMY
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DUMMY phase in auto wait flash idle transfer(RDSR).

fields.name: WAITI_CMD
fields.desc: The command value of auto wait flash idle transfer(RDSR).

fields.name: WAITI_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The dummy cycle length when wait flash idle(RDSR).

fields.name: FLASH_PER
fields.desc: program erase resume bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_PES
fields.desc: program erase suspend bit, program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to add delay time after program erase resume(PER) is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to add delay time after program erase suspend(PES) command is sent.

fields.name: PES_PER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable PES transfer trigger PES transfer option.

fields.name: PESR_IDLE_EN
fields.desc: 1: Separate PER flash wait idle and PES flash wait idle. 0: Not separate.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable auto-suspend function.

fields.name: FLASH_PER_COMMAND
fields.desc: Program/Erase resume command value.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_COMMAND
fields.desc: Program/Erase suspend command value.

fields.name: FLASH_SUS
fields.desc: The status of flash suspend. This bit is set when PES command is sent, and cleared when PER is sent. Only used in SPI1.

fields.name: FLASH_HPM_DLY_256
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 256) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after HPM command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_RES_DLY_256
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 256) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after RES command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_DP_DLY_256
fields.desc: 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 256) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after DP command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_PER_DLY_256
fields.desc: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PER_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 256) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PER command is sent.

fields.name: FLASH_PES_DLY_256
fields.desc: Valid when SPI_MEM_FLASH_PES_WAIT_EN is 1. 1: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 256) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent. 0: SPI1 waits (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES[9:0] * 4) SPI_CLK cycles after PES command is sent.

1610621096.name: TIMING_CALI
1610621096.desc: SPI1 timing compensation register when accesses to flash or Ext_RAM.

fields.name: TIMING_CALI
fields.desc: Set this bit to add extra SPI_CLK cycles in DUMMY phase for all reading operations.

fields.name: EXTRA_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: Extra SPI_CLK cycles added in DUMMY phase for timing compensation. Active when SPI_MEM_TIMING_CALI bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_EN
fields.desc: 1: in DDR mode,  0: in SDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_VAR_DUMMY
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable variable dummy cycle in DDRmode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_RDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder RX data of the word in DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_WDAT_SWP
fields.desc: Set the bit to reorder TX data of the word in DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_CMD_DIS
fields.desc: the bit is used to disable dual edge in command phase when DDR mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OUTMINBYTELEN
fields.desc: It is the minimum output data length in the panda device.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_USR_DDR_DQS_THD
fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI_CLK.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP
fields.desc: 1: Use internal signal  as data strobe, the strobe can not be delayed by input timing module. 0: Use input SPI_DQS signal from PAD as data strobe, the strobe can be delayed by input timing module

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP_MODE
fields.desc: When SPI_FMEM_DDR_DQS_LOOP and SPI_FMEM_DDR_EN are set, 1: Use internal SPI_CLK  as data strobe. 0: Use internal ~SPI_CLK  as data strobe. Otherwise this bit is not active.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_MODE
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the SPI HyperBus mode.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to flash. .

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Register clock gate enable signal. 1: Enable. 0: Disable.

fields.name: PER_END_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: PES_END_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: BROWN_OUT_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: PER_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: PES_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: BROWN_OUT_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: PER_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when Auto Resume command (0x7A) is sent and flash is resumed successfully. 0: Others.

fields.name: PES_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.1: Triggered when Auto Suspend command (0x75) is sent and flash is suspended successfully. 0: Others.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when SPI1 transfer is done and flash is already idle. When WRSR/PP/SE/BE/CE is sent and PES/PER command is sent, this bit is set when WRSR/PP/SE/BE/CE is success.  0: Others.

fields.name: BROWN_OUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered condition is that chip is loosing power and RTC module sends out brown out close flash request to SPI1. After SPI1 sends out suspend command to flash, this interrupt is triggered and MSPI returns to idle state. 0: Others.

fields.name: PER_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_PER_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: PES_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_PES_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_TOTAL_TRANS_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: BROWN_OUT_INT_ST
fields.desc: The status bit for SPI_MEM_BROWN_OUT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: SPI register version.

fields.name: CONF_BITLEN
fields.desc: Define the APB cycles of  SPI_CONF state. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: UPDATE
fields.desc: Set this bit to synchronize SPI registers from APB clock domain into SPI module clock domain, which is only used in SPI master mode.

fields.name: USR
fields.desc: User define command enable.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable. Can not be changed by CONF_buf.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_VALUE
fields.desc: Address to slave. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DUMMY_OUT
fields.desc: 0: In the dummy phase, the FSPI bus signals are not output. 1: In the dummy phase, the FSPI bus signals are output. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: Apply 2 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during addr phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_DUAL
fields.desc: Apply 2 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FREAD_OCT
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: HOLD_POL
fields.desc: SPI_HOLD output value when SPI is idle. 1: output high, 0: output low. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WP_POL
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RD_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: LSB first 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: WR_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: LSB firs 0: MSB first. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_clkcnt_N. In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1). In the slave mode it must be 0. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_clk. So spi_clk frequency is system/(spi_clkdiv_pre+1)/(spi_clkcnt_N+1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLKDIV_PRE
fields.desc: In the master mode it is pre-divider of spi_clk.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: In the master mode 1: spi_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_clk is divided from system clock. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DOUTDIN
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable full duplex communication. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: QPI_MODE
fields.desc: Both for master mode and slave mode. 1: spi controller is in QPI mode. 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: OPI_MODE
fields.desc: Just for master mode. 1: spi controller is in OPI mode (all in 8-b-m). 0: others. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: TSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of tsck. 0: tsck = spi_ck_i. 1:tsck = !spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: RSCK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode, this bit can be used to change the polarity of rsck. 0: rsck = !spi_ck_i. 1:rsck = spi_ck_i.

fields.name: CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: the bit combined with spi_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_DUAL
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_QUAD
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: FWRITE_OCT
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 8 signals. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_CONF_NXT
fields.desc: 1: Enable the DMA CONF phase of next seg-trans operation, which means seg-trans will continue. 0: The seg-trans will end after the current SPI seg-trans or this is not seg-trans mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SIO
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable 3-line half duplex communication mosi and miso signals share the same pin. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO_HIGHPART
fields.desc: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
fields.desc: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.  Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MOSI
fields.desc: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_MISO
fields.desc: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR
fields.desc: This bit enable the address phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND
fields.desc: This bit enable the command phase of an operation. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MST_WFULL_ERR_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI RX AFIFO wfull error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

fields.name: CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles+1) of prepare phase by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_setup bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: delay cycles of cs pin by spi clock this bits are combined with spi_cs_hold bit. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MST_REMPTY_ERR_END_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI transfer is ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode. 0: SPI transfer is not ended when SPI TX AFIFO read empty error is valid in GP-SPI master FD/HD-mode.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

1610760220.name: MS_DLEN
1610760220.desc: SPI data bit length control register

fields.name: MS_DATA_BITLEN
fields.desc: The value of these bits is the configured SPI transmission data bit length in master mode DMA controlled transfer or CPU controlled transfer. The value is also the configured bit length in slave mode DMA RX controlled transfer. The register value shall be (bit_num-1). Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS0_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS0 pin enable, 1: disable CS0, 0: spi_cs0 signal is from/to CS0 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS1_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS1 pin enable, 1: disable CS1, 0: spi_cs1 signal is from/to CS1 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS2_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS2 pin enable, 1: disable CS2, 0: spi_cs2 signal is from/to CS2 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS3_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS3 pin enable, 1: disable CS3, 0: spi_cs3 signal is from/to CS3 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS4_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS4 pin enable, 1: disable CS4, 0: spi_cs4 signal is from/to CS4 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS5_DIS
fields.desc: SPI CS5 pin enable, 1: disable CS5, 0: spi_cs5 signal is from/to CS5 pin. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CK_DIS
fields.desc: 1: spi clk out disable,  0: spi clk out enable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: MASTER_CS_POL
fields.desc: In the master mode the bits are the polarity of spi cs line, the value is equivalent to spi_cs ^ spi_master_cs_pol. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CLK_DATA_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI master DTR mode is applied to SPI clk, data and spi_dqs.  0: SPI master DTR mode is  only applied to spi_dqs. This bit should be used with bit 17/18/19.

fields.name: DATA_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_DOUT and SPI_DIN state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm.  0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_DOUT and SPI_DIN state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: ADDR_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_ADDR state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm.  0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_ADDR state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CMD_DTR_EN
fields.desc: 1: SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_CMD state are in DTR mode, including master 1/2/4/8-bm. 0:  SPI clk and data of SPI_SEND_CMD state are in STR mode. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: SLAVE_CS_POL
fields.desc: spi slave input cs polarity select. 1: inv  0: not change. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DQS_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: The default value of spi_dqs. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: spi clk line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: spi cs line keep low when the bit is set. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: QUAD_DIN_PIN_SWAP
fields.desc: 1: SPI quad input swap enable, swap FSPID with FSPIQ, swap FSPIWP with FSPIHD. 0:  spi quad input swap disable. Can be configured in CONF state.

fields.name: DIN0_MODE

fields.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: Records the status of DMA TX FIFO. 1: DMA TX FIFO is not ready for sending data. 0: DMA TX FIFO is ready for sending data.

fields.name: DMA_INFIFO_FULL
fields.desc: Records the status of DMA RX FIFO. 1: DMA RX FIFO is not ready for receiving data. 0: DMA RX FIFO is ready for receiving data.

fields.name: DMA_SLV_SEG_TRANS_EN
fields.desc: Enable dma segment transfer in spi dma half slave mode. 1: enable. 0: disable.

fields.name: SLV_RX_SEG_TRANS_CLR_EN
fields.desc: 1: spi_dma_infifo_full_vld is cleared by spi slave cmd 5. 0: spi_dma_infifo_full_vld is cleared by spi_trans_done.

fields.name: SLV_TX_SEG_TRANS_CLR_EN
fields.desc: 1: spi_dma_outfifo_empty_vld is cleared by spi slave cmd 6. 0: spi_dma_outfifo_empty_vld is cleared by spi_trans_done.

fields.name: RX_EOF_EN
fields.desc: 1: spi_dma_inlink_eof is set when the number of dma pushed data bytes is equal to the value of spi_slv/mst_dma_rd_bytelen[19:0] in spi dma transition.  0: spi_dma_inlink_eof is set by spi_trans_done in non-seg-trans or spi_dma_seg_trans_done in seg-trans.

fields.name: DMA_RX_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI DMA controlled receive data mode.

fields.name: DMA_TX_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI DMA controlled send data mode.

fields.name: RX_AFIFO_RST

fields.name: BUF_AFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset BUF TX AFIFO, which is used send data out in SPI slave CPU controlled mode transfer and master mode transfer.

fields.name: DMA_AFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset DMA TX AFIFO, which is used to send data out in SPI slave DMA controlled mode transfer.

fields.name: DMA_INFIFO_FULL_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: 1: The current data rate of DMA Rx is smaller than that of SPI, which will lose the receive data.  0: Others.

fields.name: DMA_OUTFIFO_EMPTY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: 1: The current data rate of DMA TX is smaller than that of SPI. SPI will stop in master mode and send out all 0 in slave mode.  0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_EX_QPI_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave Ex_QPI interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Ex_QPI transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_EN_QPI_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave En_QPI interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode En_QPI transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_CMD7_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave CMD7 interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMD7 transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_CMD8_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave CMD8 interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMD8 transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_CMD9_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave CMD9 interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMD9 transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_CMDA_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI slave CMDA interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode CMDA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_RD_DMA_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_RD_DMA_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Rd_DMA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_WR_DMA_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_WR_DMA_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Wr_DMA transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_RD_BUF_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_RD_BUF_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Rd_BUF transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_WR_BUF_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_WR_BUF_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI slave mode Wr_BUF transmission is ended. 0: Others.

fields.name: TRANS_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_TRANS_DONE_INT interrupt. 1: SPI master mode transmission is ended. 0: others.

fields.name: DMA_SEG_TRANS_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_DMA_SEG_TRANS_DONE_INT interrupt. 1:  spi master DMA full-duplex/half-duplex seg-conf-trans ends or slave half-duplex seg-trans ends. And data has been pushed to corresponding memory.  0:  seg-conf-trans or seg-trans is not ended or not occurred.

fields.name: SEG_MAGIC_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SEG_MAGIC_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The magic value in CONF buffer is error in the DMA seg-conf-trans. 0: others.

fields.name: SLV_BUF_ADDR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_BUF_ADDR_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The accessing data address of the current SPI slave mode CPU controlled FD, Wr_BUF or Rd_BUF transmission is bigger than 63. 0: Others.

fields.name: SLV_CMD_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_SLV_CMD_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: The slave command value in the current SPI slave HD mode transmission is not supported. 0: Others.

fields.name: MST_RX_AFIFO_WFULL_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MST_RX_AFIFO_WFULL_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: There is a RX AFIFO write-full error when SPI inputs data in master mode. 0: Others.

fields.name: MST_TX_AFIFO_REMPTY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MST_TX_AFIFO_REMPTY_ERR_INT interrupt. 1: There is a TX BUF AFIFO read-empty error when SPI outputs data in master mode. 0: Others.

fields.desc: RTC calibration timeout indicator

fields.desc: Cycles that release calibration timeout reset

fields.name: NTIMERS_DATE
fields.desc: Timer version control register

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Register clock gate signal. 1: The clock for software to read and write registers is always on. 0: The clock for software to read and write registers only exits when the operation happens.

fields.name: RESET_MODE
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the operating mode of the TWAI Controller. 1: Reset mode; 0: Operating mode.

fields.name: LISTEN_ONLY_MODE
fields.desc: 1: Listen only mode. In this mode the nodes will only receive messages from the bus, without generating the acknowledge signal nor updating the RX error counter.

fields.name: SELF_TEST_MODE
fields.desc: 1: Self test mode. In this mode the TX nodes can perform a successful transmission without receiving the acknowledge signal. This mode is often used to test a single node with the self reception request command.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_MODE
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the filter mode. 0: Dual filter mode; 1: Single filter mode.

fields.name: TX_REQ
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to allow the driving nodes start transmission.

fields.name: ABORT_TX
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to cancel a pending transmission request.

fields.name: RELEASE_BUF
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to release the RX buffer.

fields.name: CLR_OVERRUN
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to clear the data overrun status bit.

fields.name: SELF_RX_REQ
fields.desc: Self reception request command. Set the bit to 1 to allow a message be transmitted and received simultaneously.

fields.name: RX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: The data in the RX buffer is not empty, with at least one received data packet.

fields.name: OVERRUN_ST
fields.desc: 1: The RX FIFO is full and data overrun has occurred.

fields.name: TX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TX buffer is empty, the CPU may write a message into it.

fields.name: TX_COMPLETE
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI controller has successfully received a packet from the bus.

fields.name: RX_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI Controller is receiving a message from the bus.

fields.name: TX_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI Controller is transmitting a message to the bus.

fields.name: ERR_ST
fields.desc: 1: At least one of the RX/TX error counter has reached or exceeded the value set in register TWAI_ERR_WARNING_LIMIT_REG.

fields.name: BUS_OFF_ST
fields.desc: 1: In bus-off status, the TWAI Controller is no longer involved in bus activities.

fields.name: MISS_ST
fields.desc: This bit reflects whether the data packet in the RX FIFO is complete. 1: The current packet is missing; 0: The current packet is complete

fields.name: RX_INT_ST
fields.desc: Receive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates there are messages to be handled in the RX FIFO.

fields.name: TX_INT_ST
fields.desc: Transmit interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the message transmitting mis- sion is finished and a new transmission is able to execute.

fields.name: ERR_WARN_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error warning interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the error status signal and the bus-off status signal of Status register have changed (e.g., switched from 0 to 1 or from 1 to 0).

fields.name: OVERRUN_INT_ST
fields.desc: Data overrun interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates a data overrun interrupt is generated in the RX FIFO.

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error passive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the TWAI Controller is switched between error active status and error passive status due to the change of error counters.

fields.name: ARB_LOST_INT_ST
fields.desc: Arbitration lost interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an arbitration lost interrupt is generated.

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an error is detected on the bus.

fields.name: RX_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable receive interrupt.

fields.name: TX_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable transmit interrupt.

fields.name: ERR_WARN_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error warning interrupt.

fields.name: OVERRUN_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable data overrun interrupt.

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error passive interrupt.

fields.name: ARB_LOST_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable arbitration lost interrupt.

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error interrupt.

fields.name: BAUD_PRESC
fields.desc: Baud Rate Prescaler, determines the frequency dividing ratio.

fields.name: SYNC_JUMP_WIDTH
fields.desc: Synchronization Jump Width (SJW), 1 \verb+~+ 14 Tq wide.

fields.name: TIME_SEG1
fields.desc: The width of PBS1.

fields.name: TIME_SEG2
fields.desc: The width of PBS2.

fields.name: TIME_SAMP
fields.desc: The number of sample points. 0: the bus is sampled once; 1: the bus is sampled three times

fields.name: ARB_LOST_CAP
fields.desc: This register contains information about the bit position of lost arbitration.

fields.name: ECC_SEGMENT
fields.desc: This register contains information about the location of errors, see Table 181 for details.

fields.name: ECC_DIRECTION
fields.desc: This register contains information about transmission direction of the node when error occurs. 1: Error occurs when receiving a message; 0: Error occurs when transmitting a message

fields.name: ECC_TYPE
fields.desc: This register contains information about error types: 00: bit error; 01: form error; 10: stuff error; 11: other type of error

fields.name: ERR_WARNING_LIMIT
fields.desc: Error warning threshold. In the case when any of a error counter value exceeds the threshold, or all the error counter values are below the threshold, an error warning interrupt will be triggered (given the enable signal is valid).

fields.name: RX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The RX error counter register, reflects value changes under reception status.

fields.name: TX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The TX error counter register, reflects value changes under transmission status.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_0
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 0th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_1
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 1st byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_2
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 2nd byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_3
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 3rd byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_4
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 4th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_5
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 5th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_6
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 6th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_7
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 7th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_8
fields.desc: Stored the 8th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_9
fields.desc: Stored the 9th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_10

fields.name: TX_BYTE_11

fields.name: TX_BYTE_12

fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than what rxfifo_full_thrhd specifies.

fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in Tx-FIFO is less than what txfifo_empty_thrhd specifies .

fields.name: PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error in the data.

fields.name: FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error .

fields.name: RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than the FIFO can store.

fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of DSRn signal.

fields.name: CTS_CHG_INT_RAW

fields.name: BRK_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a 0 after the stop bit.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver takes more time than rx_tout_thrhd to receive a byte.

fields.name: SW_XON_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver recevies Xon char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_XOFF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives Xoff char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a glitch in the middle of a start bit.

fields.name: TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter completes  sending  NULL characters, after all data in Tx-FIFO are sent.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has kept the shortest duration after sending the  last data.

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has send out all data in FIFO.

fields.name: RS485_PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error from the echo of transmitter in rs485 mode.

fields.name: RS485_FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error from the echo of transmitter in rs485 mode.

fields.name: RS485_CLASH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when detects a clash between transmitter and receiver in rs485 mode.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the configured at_cmd char.

fields.name: WAKEUP_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when input rxd edge changes more times than what reg_active_threshold specifies in light sleeping mode.
