fields.desc: This is the start enable bit for IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_WCTL
fields.desc: 1'h1: The IrDA transmitter's 11th bit is the same as 10th bit. 1'h0: Set IrDA transmitter's 11th bit to 0.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of  IrDA transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_RX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the level of IrDA receiver.

fields.name: LOOPBACK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart loopback test mode.

fields.name: TX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable flow control function for transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable IrDA protocol.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart receive-FIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart transmit-FIFO.

fields.name: RXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

fields.name: CTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

fields.name: DSR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

fields.name: TXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

fields.name: RTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

fields.name: DTR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: ERR_WR_MASK
fields.desc: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

fields.name: AUTOBAUD_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for detecting baudrate.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_EN
fields.desc: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

fields.name: DIS_RX_DAT_OVF
fields.desc: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

1610612776.name: LOWPULSE
1610612776.desc: Autobaud minimum low pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the value of the minimum duration time of the low level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

1610612780.name: HIGHPULSE
1610612780.desc: Autobaud minimum high pulse duration register

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores  the value of the maxinum duration time for the high level pulse. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

fields.name: RXD_EDGE_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the count of rxd edge change. It is used in baud rate-detect process.

fields.name: SW_FLOW_CON_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

fields.name: XONOFF_DEL
fields.desc: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

fields.name: FORCE_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

fields.name: FORCE_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

fields.name: SEND_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: SEND_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

fields.name: XOFF_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xoff char.

fields.name: XOFF_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

fields.name: XON_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1, it will send a Xon char.

fields.name: XON_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

fields.name: TX_BRK_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_IDLE_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

fields.name: TX_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

fields.name: RS485_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to choose the rs485 mode.

fields.name: DL0_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: DL1_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: RS485TX_RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver could receive data when the transmitter is transmitting data in rs485 mode.

fields.name: RS485RXBY_TX_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: enable rs485 transmitter to send data when rs485 receiver line is busy.

fields.name: RS485_RX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the receiver's internal data signal.

fields.name: RS485_TX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the transmitter's internal data signal.

fields.name: PRE_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

fields.name: POST_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

fields.name: RX_GAP_TOUT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

fields.name: CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

fields.name: RX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for receive-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

fields.name: TX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated for transmit-FIFO. The default number is 128 bytes.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

1610612836.name: MEM_TX_STATUS
1610612836.desc: Tx-FIFO write and read offset address.

fields.name: APB_TX_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when software writes Tx-FIFO via APB.

fields.name: TX_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in Tx-FIFO when Tx-FSM reads data via Tx-FIFO_Ctrl.

1610612840.name: MEM_RX_STATUS
1610612840.desc: Rx-FIFO write and read offset address.

fields.name: APB_RX_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in RX-FIFO when software reads data from Rx-FIFO via APB. UART0 is 10'h200. UART1 is 10'h280. UART2 is 10'h300.

fields.name: RX_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset address in Rx-FIFO when Rx-FIFO_Ctrl writes Rx-FIFO. UART0 is 10'h200. UART1 is 10'h280. UART2 is 10'h300.

fields.name: ST_URX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of receiver.

fields.name: ST_UTX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of transmitter.

fields.name: POSEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two positive edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

fields.name: NEGEDGE_MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the minimal input clock count between two negative edges. It is used in boudrate-detect process.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_B
fields.desc: The  denominator of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_A
fields.desc: The numerator of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: SCLK_SEL
fields.desc: UART clock source select. 1: 80Mhz, 2: 8Mhz, 3: XTAL.

fields.name: SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Tx/Rx clock.

fields.name: RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx/Rx.

fields.name: TX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Tx clock.

fields.name: RX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Rx clock.

fields.name: TX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Tx.

fields.name: RX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit, reset UART Rx.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version register.

fields.name: ID
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the uart_id.

fields.name: HIGH_SPEED
fields.desc: This bit used to select synchronize mode. 1: Registers are auto synchronized into UART Core clock and UART core should be keep the same with APB clock. 0: After configure registers, software needs to write 1 to UART_REG_UPDATE to synchronize registers.

fields.name: REG_UPDATE
fields.desc: Software write 1 would synchronize registers into UART Core clock domain and would be cleared by hardware after synchronization is done.

fields.name: TX_RST
fields.desc: Write 1, then write 0 to this bit to reset decode state machine.

fields.name: RX_RST
fields.desc: Write 1, then write 0 to this bit to reset encode state machine.

fields.name: UART0_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to link up HCI and UART0.

fields.name: UART1_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to link up HCI and UART1.

fields.name: UART2_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to link up HCI and UART2.

fields.name: SEPER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to separate the data frame using a special char.

fields.name: HEAD_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode the data packet with a formatting header.

fields.name: CRC_REC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UHCI to receive the 16 bit CRC.

fields.name: UART_IDLE_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI will end the payload receiving process when UART has been in idle state.

fields.name: LEN_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI decoder receiving payload data is end when the receiving byte count has reached the specified value. The value is payload length indicated by UHCI packet header when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 1 or the value is configuration value when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 0. If this bit is set to 0, UHCI decoder receiving payload data is end when 0xc0 is received.

fields.name: ENCODE_CRC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable data integrity checking by appending a 16 bit CCITT-CRC to end of the payload.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1'b1: Force clock on for register. 1'b0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: UART_RX_BRK_EOF_EN
fields.desc: If this bit is set to 1, UHCI will end payload receive process when NULL frame is received by UART.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when a separator char has been sent.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when UHCI detects a separator char.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when UHCI takes more time to receive data than configure value.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when UHCI takes more time to read data from RAM than the configured value.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when UHCI has sent out a short packet using single_send registers.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when UHCI has sent out a short packet using always_send registers.

fields.name: OUT_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when there are some errors in EOF in the transmit data.

fields.name: APP_CTRL0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when set UHCI_APP_CTRL0_IN_SET.

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This is the interrupt raw bit. Triggered when set UHCI_APP_CTRL1_IN_SET.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_RX_START_INT interrupt when UHCI_RX_START_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_TX_START_INT interrupt when UHCI_TX_START_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt when UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT interrupt when UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_SEND_S_REQ_Q_INT interrupt when UHCI_SEND_S_REQ_Q_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_SEND_A_REQ_Q_INT interrupt when UHCI_SEND_A_REQ_Q_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT interrupt when UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: APP_CTRL0_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT interrupt when UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the masked interrupt bit for UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT interrupt when UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT_ENA  is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_RX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_TX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_SEND_S_REQ_Q_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_SEND_A_REQ_Q_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: APP_CTRL0_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT interrupt.

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the interrupt enable bit for UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT interrupt.

fields.name: RX_START_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_RX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_START_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_TX_START_INT interrupt.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: TX_HUNG_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SEND_S_REG_Q_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_SEND_S_REQ_Q_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SEND_A_REG_Q_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_SEND_A_REQ_Q_INT interrupt.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: APP_CTRL0_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT interrupt.

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT interrupt.

fields.name: APP_CTRL0_INT_SET
fields.desc: This bit is software interrupt trigger source of UHCI_APP_CTRL0_INT.

fields.name: APP_CTRL1_INT_SET
fields.desc: This bit is software interrupt trigger source of UHCI_APP_CTRL1_INT.

fields.name: CHECK_SUM_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to check header checksum when UHCI receives a data packet.

fields.name: CHECK_SEQ_EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit to check sequence number when UHCI receives a data packet.

fields.name: CRC_DISABLE
fields.desc: Set this bit to support CRC calculation. Data Integrity Check Present bit in UHCI packet frame should be 1.

fields.name: SAVE_HEAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to save the packet header when HCI receives a data packet.

fields.name: TX_CHECK_SUM_RE
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode the data packet with a checksum.

fields.name: TX_ACK_NUM_RE
fields.desc: Set this bit to encode the data packet with an acknowledgment when a reliable packet is to be transmit.

fields.name: WAIT_SW_START
fields.desc: The uhci-encoder will jump to ST_SW_WAIT status if this register is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_START
fields.desc: If current UHCI_ENCODE_STATE is ST_SW_WAIT, the UHCI will start to send data packet out when this bit is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_ERR_CAUSE
fields.desc: This register indicates the error type when DMA has received a packet with error. 3'b001: Checksum error in HCI packet. 3'b010: Sequence number error in HCI packet. 3'b011: CRC bit error in HCI packet. 3'b100: 0xc0 is found but received HCI packet is not end. 3'b101: 0xc0 is not found when receiving HCI packet is end. 3'b110: CRC check error.

fields.name: DECODE_STATE
fields.desc: UHCI decoder status.

fields.name: ENCODE_STATE
fields.desc: UHCI encoder status.

fields.name: TX_C0_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable decoding char 0xc0 when DMA receives data.

fields.name: TX_DB_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable decoding char 0xdb when DMA receives data.

fields.name: TX_11_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable decoding flow control char 0x11 when DMA receives data.

fields.name: TX_13_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable decoding flow control char 0x13 when DMA receives data.

fields.name: RX_C0_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable replacing 0xc0 by special char when DMA sends data.

fields.name: RX_DB_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable replacing 0xdb by special char when DMA sends data.

fields.name: RX_11_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable replacing flow control char 0x11 by special char when DMA sends data.

fields.name: RX_13_ESC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable replacing flow control char 0x13 by special char when DMA sends data.

fields.name: TXFIFO_TIMEOUT
fields.desc: This register stores the timeout value. It will produce the UHCI_TX_HUNG_INT interrupt when DMA takes more time to receive data.

fields.name: TXFIFO_TIMEOUT_SHIFT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the tick count maximum value.

fields.name: TXFIFO_TIMEOUT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for Tx-FIFO receive-data timeout.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TIMEOUT
fields.desc: This register stores the timeout value. It will produce the UHCI_RX_HUNG_INT interrupt when DMA takes more time to read data from RAM.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TIMEOUT_SHIFT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the tick count maximum value.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TIMEOUT_ENA
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for DMA send-data timeout.

fields.name: ACK_NUM
fields.desc: This ACK number used in software flow control.

fields.name: LOAD
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1, the value configured by UHCI_ACK_NUM would be loaded.

fields.name: RX_HEAD
fields.desc: This register stores the header of the current received packet.

fields.name: SINGLE_SEND_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to specify the single_send register.

fields.name: SINGLE_SEND_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable single_send mode to send short packet.

fields.name: ALWAYS_SEND_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to specify the always_send register.

fields.name: ALWAYS_SEND_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable always_send mode to send short packet.

fields.name: SEND_Q0_WORD0
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q0_WORD1
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q1_WORD0
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q1_WORD1
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q2_WORD0
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q2_WORD1
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q3_WORD0
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q3_WORD1
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q4_WORD0
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q4_WORD1
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q5_WORD0
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q5_WORD1
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q6_WORD0
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEND_Q6_WORD1
fields.desc: This register is used as a quick_sent register when specified by UHCI_ALWAYS_SEND_NUM or UHCI_SINGLE_SEND_NUM.

fields.name: SEPER_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to define the separate char that need to be encoded, default is 0xc0.

fields.name: SEPER_ESC_CHAR0
fields.desc: This register is used to define the first char of slip escape sequence when encoding the separate char, default is 0xdb.

fields.name: SEPER_ESC_CHAR1
fields.desc: This register is used to define the second char of slip escape sequence when encoding the separate char, default is 0xdc.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ0
fields.desc: This register is used to define a char that need to be encoded, default is 0xdb that used as the first char of slip escape sequence.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ0_CHAR0
fields.desc: This register is used to define the first char of slip escape sequence when encoding the UHCI_ESC_SEQ0, default is 0xdb.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ0_CHAR1
fields.desc: This register is used to define the second char of slip escape sequence when encoding the UHCI_ESC_SEQ0, default is 0xdd.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ1
fields.desc: This register is used to define a char that need to be encoded, default is 0x11 that used as flow control char.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ1_CHAR0
fields.desc: This register is used to define the first char of slip escape sequence when encoding the UHCI_ESC_SEQ1, default is 0xdb.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ1_CHAR1
fields.desc: This register is used to define the second char of slip escape sequence when encoding the UHCI_ESC_SEQ1, default is 0xde.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ2
fields.desc: This register is used to define a char that need to be decoded, default is 0x13 that used as flow control char.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ2_CHAR0
fields.desc: This register is used to define the first char of slip escape sequence when encoding the UHCI_ESC_SEQ2, default is 0xdb.

fields.name: ESC_SEQ2_CHAR1
fields.desc: This register is used to define the second char of slip escape sequence when encoding the UHCI_ESC_SEQ2, default is 0xdf.

fields.name: PKT_THRS
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum value of the packet length when UHCI_HEAD_EN is 0.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version control register.

fields.name: RDWR_BYTE
fields.desc: Write and read byte data to/from UART Tx/Rx FIFO through this field. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_IN_EMPTY_INT is set, then user can write data (up to 64 bytes) into UART Tx FIFO. When USB_DEVICE_SERIAL_OUT_RECV_PKT_INT is set, user can check USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP1_WR_ADDR USB_DEVICE_OUT_EP0_RD_ADDR to know how many data is received, then read data from UART Rx FIFO.

fields.name: WR_DONE
fields.desc: Set this bit to indicate writing byte data to UART Tx FIFO is done.

fields.name: SERIAL_IN_EP_DATA_FREE
fields.desc: 1'b1: Indicate UART Tx FIFO is not full and can write data into in. After writing USB_DEVICE_WR_DONE, this bit would be 0 until data in UART Tx FIFO is read by USB Host.

fields.name: SERIAL_OUT_EP_DATA_AVAIL
fields.desc: 1'b1: Indicate there is data in UART Rx FIFO.

fields.name: PLAIN
fields.desc: Stores the nth 32-bit piece of plaintext.

fields.name: LINESIZE
fields.desc: Configures the data size of one encryption.

fields.name: DESTINATION
fields.desc: Configures the type of the external memory. Currently, it must be set to 0, as the Manual Encryption block only supports flash encryption. Errors may occurs if users write 1. 0:flash. 1: external RAM.

fields.name: PHYSICAL_ADDRESS
fields.desc: Those bits stores the physical address. If linesize is 16-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 16 bytes. If linesize is 32-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 32 bytes. If linesize is 64-byte, the physical address should be aligned of 64 bytes.

fields.name: TRIGGER
fields.desc: Write 1 to activate manual encryption.

fields.name: RELEASE
fields.desc: Write 1 to grant SPI1 access to encrypted result.

fields.name: DESTROY
fields.desc: Write 1 to destroy encrypted result.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: Those bits indicates the status of the Manual Encryption block. 0X0 (XTS_AES_IDLE): idle. 0X1 (XTS_AES_BUSY): busy with encryption. 0X2 (XTS_AES_DONE): encryption is completed, but the encrypted result is not accessible to SPI. 0X3 (XTS_AES_AVAILABLE) encrypted result is accessible and available to SPI.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Manual Encryption block version information.
